It's Monday! That means a new episode of Dear Gabby has dropped and I've got your weekly card reading for you!

On today’s episode of Dear Gabby, I break it down for you. I’ll reveal my method to stop resisting the good things in your life.

>>> You’ll learn how to transform your fear-based beliefs into faith.

>>> Discover 3 ways to show up for yourself, an amazing technique to release judgment and shame, and powerful tools to live a Super Attractor life!

>>> And I share a prayer that helps you offer your fear over to the Universe and claim your desire to feel good.

Here’s the deal: No matter how hard things can be, we always have the power within us to turn our life around.

Today I’ll show you how.

🎙️Check out Dear Gabby episode 14 now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link in bio!

I’m going to make meditation EASY, fun and something you become OBSESSED WITH! 

Here’s how:

I’m leading a Meditation Challenge!

Starting August 1 I’ll be your meditation coach for 21 days. 

You’ll get: 
21 daily meditations (different styles each day) 
Exclusive member platform and downloadable journal 
Daily emails to keep you on track (plus text support if you want) 
Community support (literally the coolest group ever!) 
A live training session with me on Day 21! 
Let me help you make meditation easy.

Link in bio @gabbybernstein 

The meditation challenge is perfect for you if you’re ready to … 

Stick to your meditation practice.
Learn to meditate or amp up your existing practice. 

Feel awesome! You’ll be amazed at how good it feels when you commit to a daily meditation practice. 

Attract more of what you want! When you feel good, you attract solutions, come up with inspired ideas and much, much more!

Get motivated—you can speed up by slowing down. 

Stop focusing on problems and attract solutions. Meditating daily will help you see spiritual guidance in everything around you.

Let’s do this! Join now at the link in bio @gabbybernstein

node.text:
In this week's episode of Dear Gabby I teach one of the fastest ways to let go of control. It’s an old Dear Gabby method from 2006! 

This OG method is called the 3 Rs and it’s designed to help you rapidly process and release uncomfortable feelings in 90 seconds! 

The 3 Rs stands for Recognize, Record, Release.

It’s simple. All you need is to have a small journal on hand throughout the day. (Or you can use the Notes app in your iPhone.)

The next time you notice a negative controlling thought come up, do this:

Recognize: Notice the thought.
Record: Write it down in a journal.
Release: Say a prayer, “Thank you, Universe, for transforming this fear and helping me release it now.”

On the podcast I break this method down even further. (Link in bio)

node.text:
Resilience is our ability to recover from difficult situations and adapt to change. We often talk about “bouncing back” — that is resilience.

When you think of how to be more resilient, picture a reed: It’s strong, but it’s also flexible. It doesn’t resist the wind and the wind doesn’t break it. The reed moves with the wind.

A big part of becoming more resilient is strengthening our faith and turning over our fears every single day, one step at a time. 

This was such a beautiful conversation on Ep. 15 of Dear Gabby and one I know will serve every single person that listens! Tune in now on Apple/Spotify or anywhere podcasts are streamed!

Last call!! The Meditation Challenge starts tomorrow!! Eeek!

In just 21 days you can calm stress, get grounded, and feel good no matter what’s going on.

And I’ll guide you every step of the way. 

If you can’t meditate right now because of all the fear and anxiety — this challenge is for you.

If you’ve never meditated before — this challenge is for you.

If you’re struggling with anxiety — this challenge is for you. 

If you feel unmotivated — this challenge is for you.

If you feel alone and disconnected — this challenge is for you. 

If you’re trying to meditate daily but still feel stuck — this challenge is for you.

If you’re afraid of the future — this challenge is for you.

If you’re ready to stop doing so much and start receiving — this challenge is for you.

I want to be your meditation coach and help guide you. 

Click the link in my bio @gabbybernstein

T-minus 3 days to join the 21-day Meditation Challenge (link in bio @gabbybernstein) 

One of the most important promises of meditation is that when you change your energy, you change the energy of the world. That’s not some spiritual mumbo-jumbo — it’s truth.

Here’s an example: You meditate in the morning and shift your energy. You start your day feeling better. That afternoon, you call a friend and bring positive energy to the conversation. She feels better and is more connected to her children as a result. Her children feel the connection and are more centered and strong.

When you meditate, it has a ripple effect that helps others and changes the energetic state of the world.

Meditation is a gift to yourself and a gift to the world. Your greatest contribution is your energy. 

I'm committed to supporting you as you establish your meditation practice, get back on track with it or simply strengthen it. Let's elevate our energy and serve the world together. 🌍

Join me for my first 21-day Meditation Challenge. It starts THIS Sunday, August 1.

Sign up by clicking the link in my bio @gabbybernstein
Or go to DearGabby.com/meditationchallenge

How do you channel the stream of love? You meditate. 👇👇👇👇

👉👉👉The meditation challenge starts This Sunday! 

If you’ve fallen off with your meditation practice, I have three steps to get you back on track! 

It doesn’t matter whether you’ve gone days or months (or years) without meditating. You can change the pattern today.

Step 1: Ask yourself, ‘How do I want to feel?’

If you find yourself resisting the idea of meditating, pause for just a moment. Ask yourself how you want to feel and connect with your desire. Whatever it is, meditation will clear the path. When we take a little time each day (even just a few minutes) to quiet our mind, the rewards are massive.

Step 2: Forgive yourself for falling off track

If you get into that story of, “I suck, I can’t believe I fell off again, I’m not good enough,” then you won’t get back on.
So just forgive yourself right away and remember that you can get back into meditating regularly at any moment of any day.

Step 3: Meditate!

I want to support you in your commitment to meditate regularly. That’s why I created my 21-Day Meditation Challenge.

During this 21-day challenge, I’ll give you a simple, structured, daily practice that will get you excited about meditation and make it easy for you to apply.

I’ve laid out the plan for you and I’ll guide you every step of the way. You don’t need to overthink it. You don’t need to be the perfect meditator. And it doesn’t matter whether you have an established practice or you’re a complete beginner.

All you have to do is show up. By the end of the challenge, you’ll feel empowered and energized, able to soothe and ground yourself just by turning inward.

Only 4 days left to join! Sign up for the Meditation Challenge now! Link in bio @gabbybernstein or at gabbybernstein.com/meditationchallenge
